<item>
            <title>[PIG-2069] LoadFunc jar does not ship to backend in MultiQuery case</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2069</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Pig is able to automatically figure out the jar containing the LoadFunc and ship them to backend. However, the following script didn&apos;t:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
A = load &apos;1.txt&apos; using SomeLoadFunc();
B = filter A by $0==0;
C = filter A by $1==1;
D = join B by $0, C by $0;
dump D;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason is this query is a multiquery (A is reused and thus create an implicit split). When we merge multiquery into one job, we didn&apos;t merge udfs list properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
